{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/css-clamp-min-max/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Jonas Gustavsson"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"ea0d78a8-61d3-5df5-b730-45ebe227b28c","excerpt":"min() The  lets you set the smallest value from a list of values.\nFor example: With this our box will have a width of  or . Whichever is the smallest. If  (5…","html":"<h2 id=\"min\" style=\"position:relative;\">min()</h2>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">min()</code> lets you set the smallest value from a list of values.\nFor example:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.box</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">width</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">min</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>50vw<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 500px<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>With this our box will have a width of <code class=\"language-text\">50vw</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">500px</code>. Whichever is the smallest.</p>\n<p>If <code class=\"language-text\">50vw</code> (50% of the viewport width) computes to a lower value than <code class=\"language-text\">500px</code> the element will be <code class=\"language-text\">50vw</code> wide.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; margin-left: 0; max-width: 450px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/13b08a53c1e34480a843ddfbc4b7067d/21b4d/min.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.83185840707964%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"min\"\n        title=\"min\"\n        src=\"/static/13b08a53c1e34480a843ddfbc4b7067d/fc2a6/min.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/13b08a53c1e34480a843ddfbc4b7067d/2519b/min.png 113w,\n/static/13b08a53c1e34480a843ddfbc4b7067d/3684f/min.png 225w,\n/static/13b08a53c1e34480a843ddfbc4b7067d/fc2a6/min.png 450w,\n/static/13b08a53c1e34480a843ddfbc4b7067d/23296/min.png 675w,\n/static/13b08a53c1e34480a843ddfbc4b7067d/1cfc2/min.png 900w,\n/static/13b08a53c1e34480a843ddfbc4b7067d/21b4d/min.png 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In the example above the viewport is 600 pixels wide. <code class=\"language-text\">min(50vw, 500px)</code> will therefore return <code class=\"language-text\">50vw</code> because 50% of 600 pixels is 300 pixels. And 300 is less than 500.</p>\n<h2 id=\"max\" style=\"position:relative;\">max()</h2>\n<p>Works much the same as its brother <code class=\"language-text\">min()</code> but it picks the largest value from a list of values.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.box</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">width</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">max</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>50vw<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 500px<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; margin-left: 0; max-width: 450px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/280aa5114fa2f6b6f3a56140b91e17bf/21b4d/max.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.83185840707964%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"max\"\n        title=\"max\"\n        src=\"/static/280aa5114fa2f6b6f3a56140b91e17bf/fc2a6/max.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/280aa5114fa2f6b6f3a56140b91e17bf/2519b/max.png 113w,\n/static/280aa5114fa2f6b6f3a56140b91e17bf/3684f/max.png 225w,\n/static/280aa5114fa2f6b6f3a56140b91e17bf/fc2a6/max.png 450w,\n/static/280aa5114fa2f6b6f3a56140b91e17bf/23296/max.png 675w,\n/static/280aa5114fa2f6b6f3a56140b91e17bf/1cfc2/max.png 900w,\n/static/280aa5114fa2f6b6f3a56140b91e17bf/21b4d/max.png 1280w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In this example our box gets a width of 500 pixels. Because 500 is greater than 300 (50% of the viewport).</p>\n<h2 id=\"clamp\" style=\"position:relative;\">clamp()</h2>\n<p>Clamp is effectively a combination of the <code class=\"language-text\">min()</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">max()</code> functions. It accepts three parameters:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>minimum value</li>\n<li>preferred value</li>\n<li>maximum value</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Consider this:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.box</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token property\">width</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token function\">clamp</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>400px<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 50vw<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 1200px<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This will ensure three things:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The width will never go below <code class=\"language-text\">400px</code>.</li>\n<li>The width will be <code class=\"language-text\">50vw</code> as long as it’s not smaller than <code class=\"language-text\">400px</code> or larger than <code class=\"language-text\">1200px</code>.</li>\n<li>The width will never go above <code class=\"language-text\">1200px</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In other words, this makes it so that the box’s width is <code class=\"language-text\">50vw</code> but never smaller than <code class=\"language-text\">400px</code> or larger than <code class=\"language-text\">1200px</code>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"CSS responsive design with clamp min & max","date":"October 03, 2020","description":"A very welcome addition to our arsenal of responsive design tools. The min() max() and clamp() functions are now supported in all major browsers. "}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/css-clamp-min-max/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/optional-chaining/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Cleaner JavaScript with optional chaining"}},"next":null}}}